{
  "stem": "19218.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 297.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of the Jewish names are actually Hebrew names.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So his Hebrew name was [HEBREW], but he was called Hersh.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother's name was Dyna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had-- my oldest sister's name was Rochell, which is Rachel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My brother, which was next-- excuse me, but I'm closing up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My throat is closing up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This is what happens when I talk about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[DRINKS] My brother's name was-- since he passed away about five years ago, [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Lazer, ?] or Eliezer in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was the youngest, as I said, of four children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my-- and I had a sister, which was just one year older than I was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Her name was Ester.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We lived, of course, in that town until the war from 1939.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] My grandfather's name [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was Moses.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "His name was actually Moshe [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My grandmother's name was Faige.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My grandfather died, I'd say, approximately in 1929.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember it because he called me-- and I was his grandson-- and he said, I want-- I want you to go and call Bubbe and tell her that I'm going to die.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And this-- I didn't even understand what dying meant, I guess, at that time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But I retained this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I mean, I-- I have a picture of this, remembering it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And he died that particular day also.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My grandma, Faige, or Faige as they called her, she died about, I'd say, two years after my grandfather died.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I never knew [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the grandparents on my mother's side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They all undoubtedly passed away before I was born.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- the war started in September of 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
